 South Africans have begun fresh attacks, looting and burning of businesses and properties belonging to foreigners and in the process killed three people, while another is still receiving treatment for smoke inhalation. September 2, 2019 In "News" Three people have been reportedly killed and many property destroyed in an attack on foreigners, including Nigerians based in South Africa. September 3, 2019 In "News" Police in Johannesburg, yesterday, said many shops were ransacked in Johannesburg, overnight, in the latest wave of looting in South African cities. February 28, 2017 In "News"